resumé.description: Participated in a 6-week intensive challenge at Chas Academy, where I collaborated with a team to develop a fullstack application using C#, .NET, and React. This experience honed my skills in Agile methodologies, teamwork, and project management.
Over seven years of painting experience, including restoration projects requiring precision and care, as well as managing and completing projects efficiently.
Started as an apprentice, demonstrating drive and dedication through proactive efforts to secure the position.
Responsible for passenger safety, gaining valuable experience in customer service and managing sensitive situations.

education.description: This program focuses on the C# programming language. This gives me skills in creating and maintaining web and business applications. The program includes both frontend development and backend development with APIs and microservices as well as database management. It also includes Agile methodology, which is a way of working that is used in many companies today.

With this program, I learned the fundamental knowledge needed for programming. In addition, the ability to identify, fix, and prevent syntax errors, program runtime errors, and programming logic errors is developed.

3 years working as an apprentice in this branch I´ve learned how to understand the dynamic of junior and a senior. How important it is to have ambition and focus in learning and being able to admit when I´ve made misstakes.
Attention to details and precisition is a must. Here I've learned how to both read, draw blueprints and build furnitures from scratch.
